CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 24, 1961, pg. 24, reads: "For A Great Cause - Even though the turnout for the Maurice Stokes benefit at Syria Mosque was small, outstanding personalities from the field of entertainment turned out for the event... Photo on the right shows radio station WAMO newscaster Charles Gordon interviewing Jack Twyman and Miss Kitt. Twyman has served as guardian for Stokes during the former cage star's illness. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: WAMO radio station newscaster Charles Gordon interviewing Eartha Kitt, for Maurice Stokes benefit in Syria Mosque
